<h2>About ApxrIo</h2>

<p>
  ApxrIo is a project manager for the BEAM ecosystem, any language that compiles to run on the BEAM VM, such as <a href="https://elixir-lang.org/">Elixir</a> and <a href="http://www.erlang.org/">Erlang</a>, can be used to build ApxrIo projects.
  ApxrIo consists of the <a href="https://github.com/apxr_io/specifications/blob/master/http_api.md">HTTP API</a>, <a href="/">this website</a>, the repository serving projects and indexes, <a href="https://hexdocs.pm">hexdocs</a>, the <a href="https://github.com/apxr_io/apxr_io">Mix build-tool integration</a>, and <a href="https://github.com/apxr_io">other services</a>.
  Many build tools support ApxrIo projects including <a href="https://hexdocs.pm/mix">Mix</a> for Elixir projects, <a href="https://www.rebar3.org/">Rebar</a> and <a href="https://erlang.mk/">erlang.mk</a> for Erlang projects.
</p>

